<HEAD>Shirley Temple Black Calls President Reagan A Good Kisser</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Former child star Shirley Temple Black has a
different sort of kiss-and-tell story than the White House insider
books that have come out of Washington recently.
   She says Ronald Reagan was really a good kisser.
   The two performed together in a nearly forgotten 1947 film ``That
Hagen Girl.'' At the time, she was a teen-ager and he was the
leading man.
   ``He was one of the best kissers,'' Ms. Black said Tuesday in an
interview televised on the syndicated ``Entertainment Tonight.''
   In the film, Ms. Black's character feared that the teacher played
by the future president was her illegitimate father.
   The film was ``probably one of the worst movies either one of us
ever made,'' said Ms. Black, who is promoting her autobiography,
``Child Star.''
   On New Year's Day, Ms. Black, 60, will be grand marshal of the
100th Annual Tournament of Roses Parade in Pasadena.
   She was grand marshal of the 50th annual parade in 1939 at age 10.
