<HEAD>Bolinas Sign Confiscated As Evidence Stolen Yet Again</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOLINAS, Calif. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   At this rate, no one will ever know the
way to Bolinas.
   The sign pointing the way to Bolinas that was confiscated for
evidence in connection with the arrest of two men for investigation
of stealing the marker has been stolen again, the California Highway
Patrol said Tuesday.
   It was the 35th time the sign on Route 1 had been put up since
the placards began disappearing about 20 years ago on the road
leading to this secluded beach town 15 miles north of San Francisco.
   On Friday, officers spotted two men tearing down the 3-by-9-foot
sign. After the suspects were arrested, the officers left the sign
at the scene as they went to get a larger vehicle to carry it to the
evidence locker.
   ``When they returned with a vehicle capable of transporting it,
it wasn't there,'' said Officer Mark Pieschke.
