<1ST_LINE>r a PM-AIDSSlaying     10-26 0340</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-AIDS Slaying,0351</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Man Sentenced For Slaying Of Roommate Over AIDS</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By COLLEEN BARRY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>DENVER (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man who believed his roommate infected him with
the AIDS virus was sentenced to 28 years in prison for killing the
man.
   Frank Ford, 31, testified at his sentencing hearing that he moved
in with former Air Force Sgt. James L. Wiggins in March with the
sole intent of killing Wiggins after learning he tested positive for
the AIDS virus.
   ``I confronted (Wiggins). I said, `Hey, you gave me the AIDS
virus,' and all he could do was laugh in my face. He laughed in my
face about it,'' Ford said. ``I gave this lady friend that means a
lot to me the AIDS virus, and all he could do was laugh in my face,
like so what?
   ``That's when I decided to kill him.''
   Ford pleaded guilty on Sept. 2 to manslaughter for Wiggins'
bludgeoning death on April 2. He pleaded guilty to first-degree
assault and aggravated motor vehicle theft.
   ``Mr. Ford is probably going to suffer severely and die in the
Department of Corrections,'' Denver District Judge Lynn Hufnagel
said Tuesday. ``That is, I suppose a much worse punishment than this
court could ever impose.
   ``What kind of sentence do you think you should get?'' she asked.
``It doesn't seem to make a lot of difference does it?''
   Ford replied, ``No, it doesn't.''
   Ford and Wiggins met in an adult bookstore in 1986. Ford said he
is not a homosexual, but agreed to have sex with Wiggins for money.
   Their relationship was interrupted when Ford was sent to prison
on a theft conviction. It was there that Ford tested positive for
the AIDS virus.
   Acquired immune deficiency syndrome is a fatal disease that
breaks down the body's immune system
   The prosecution had sought a 40-year sentence, citing five
previous felony convictions and the manner in which Ford disposed of
Wiggins' body. Testimony showed Ford stuffed the body into a
footlocker and dumped it into a lake.
</TEXT>
