imprisonment for killing Sikhs in riots after the assassination of
Prime Minister Indira Gandhi, news reports said Wednesday.
   Tuesday's sentences were the first in connection with the riots
that killed at least 3,000 people, mostly Sikhs, during three days
after Mrs. Gandhi's slaying on Oct. 31, 1984, according to the The
