<HEAD>Atlanta Journal Endorses Bush</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Atlanta Journal on Wednesday endorsed
Republican George Bush for president, arguing that the vice
president represents ``leadership with proven results in foreign
policy, at the pay window and at income tax time.''
   The Journal's sister newspaper, The Atlanta Constitution, last
week endorsed Democratic presidential nominee Michael Dukakis.
   The Journal said Bush and Dukakis offer the voters a choice
between ``experience and experimentation and between proven values
and those rejected in the last two national elections.''
   ``Values and leadership put a stamp on a candidacy,'' the
newspaper said. ``George Bush has been principled and consistent.
His uncompromising stands against crime and for the enhancement of
families contrast well with liberal social experimentation.''
   

