<DOCNO> AP881026-0235 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-10-26-88 0935EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>u f BC-Britain-Stocks     10-26 0117</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Britain-Stocks,0123</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>London Stocks Higher In Light Trading</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices were higher at midday Wednesday, but
trading was sluggish amid nervousness ahead of Thursday's release of
British trade figures for September.
   The market's positive tone came in part from a steady trend in
sterling and British government bonds, dealers said. Recent weakness
in the pound hit equities earlier in the week as worries surfaced
that interest rates might be pushed higher to support the British
currency.
   The Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-stock index was up 7.1
points, or 0.4 percent, at 1,854.9 at midday.
   Volume was thin, with just 224.4 million shares changing hands,
compared with 214.9 million shares at the same time Tuesday.
</TEXT>
