<1ST_LINE>u f PM-Earns-Bethlehem     10-26 0181</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Earns-Bethlehem,0189</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Profit More Than Triples</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BETHLEHEM, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bethlehem Steel Corp. today said its
third-quarter profit more than tripled on the strength of the steel
industry's recovery.
   Net income for the period rose to $101.4 million, or $1.18 per
share, up from $30.4 million, or 46 cents per share, a year earlier.
Third-quarter sales rose 23.3 percent to $1.43 billion from $1.16
billion a year earlier.
   Bethlehem attributed its improved performance to increased
shipments, higher productivity and prices and lower financing costs.
   ``We expect our steel shipments to continue at relatively strong
levels through the balance of the year and our prices to remain
firm,'' said Chairman Walter F. Williams. ``There has been some
softening in our order entry ... but we believe it to be a temporary
situation as underlying steel consumption remains strong.''
   For the first nine months, the company earned $337.3 million, or
$4.17 per share, up nearly three times compared to $102.8 million,
or $1.61 per share, a year earlier.
   Nine-month sale rose 22 percent to $4.16 billion from $3.41
billion a year earlier.
</TEXT>
