<HEAD>TRW Directors Elect Joseph T. Gorman As Chairman</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: SUBS 3rd graf pvs Last February... to CORRECT spelling to
Mettler sted Metler.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>CLEVELAND (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   TRW Inc. said Wednesday it has elected Joseph T.
Gorman to be chairman of the defense contractor.
   Gorman, currently president and chief executive officer, will
succeed Ruben F. Mettler, 64, who is retiring effective Dec. 1.
   Last February, TRW's board of directors announced its intention
to name Gorman to succeed Mettler. Gorman, 51, will retain the title
of president when he becomes chairman.
   Gorman joined TRW in 1968, was elected secretary of the company
in 1970, vice president in 1972, and vice president and general
counsel in 1976.
